---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Fujifilm X-S20 vs X-T5 — cameraupick" description="Compare Fujifilm X-S20 vs X-T5: video features vs classic handling, stabilization, and which shooter each suits.">
<section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h1>Fujifilm X-S20 vs X-T5</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">Same lenses, different priorities: video tools vs classic photo handling.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-media">
          <img src="/assets/images/compare/fuji-xs20-vs-xt5.webp" alt="Fujifilm X-S20 vs X-T5 comparison"
            loading="eager">
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="section">
      <h2>TL;DR picks</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card" id="fuji-x-s20">
          <div class="tag">Pick</div>
          <h3>X-S20</h3>
          <p>Best for video/vlog and travel. Flip screen, better thermals, vlog mode.</p>
          <div class="quick-actions">
            <a class="buy-btn" href="https://example.com/affiliate/x-s20" rel="nofollow">Best deal</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card" id="fuji-x-t5">
          <div class="tag">Photo-first</div>
          <h3>X-T5</h3>
          <p>40MP stills, classic dials, tilt screen. Great for photo-first shooters.</p>
          <div class="quick-actions">
            <a class="buy-btn" href="https://example.com/affiliate/x-t5" rel="nofollow">Shop X-T5</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="tag">Budget</div>
          <h3>X-S10 (used)</h3>
          <p>Cheaper body with IBIS and solid video if you find a good used price.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
            style="margin-top:10px; display:inline-block; font-size:14px;">Check Price on Amazon &rarr;</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Quick comparison</h2>
      <table class="compare-table">
        <tr>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>X-S20</th>
          <th>X-T5</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Best for</td>
          <td>Video, vlogging, travel</td>
          <td>Photo-first, high-res stills</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Screen</td>
          <td>Fully articulating</td>
          <td>3-way tilt</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Resolution</td>
          <td>26MP</td>
          <td>40MP</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Video</td>
          <td>4K60, better thermals, vlog mode</td>
          <td>6.2K open-gate, more rolling shutter</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Stabilization</td>
          <td>IBIS tuned for handheld video</td>
          <td>IBIS tuned for stills</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Ergonomics</td>
          <td>PASM dial, lighter body</td>
          <td>Classic shutter/ISO dials</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Scores</h2>
      <div class="rating-grid">
        <div class="score-card"><span class="score">8.6</span><span class="score-label">Overall (X-S20)</span></div>
        <div class="score-card"><span class="score">8.9</span><span class="score-label">Photo (X-T5)</span></div>
        <div class="score-card"><span class="score">8.4</span><span class="score-label">Video (X-S20)</span></div>
        <div class="score-card"><span class="score">8.1</span><span class="score-label">Value (X-S20)</span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Who should buy each</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Choose X-S20 if…</h3>
          <p>You film often, need a flip screen, and want easier handheld video with forgiving thermals. Great for
            travel vloggers and hybrid shooters on APS-C.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
            style="margin-top:10px; display:inline-block; font-size:14px;">Check Price on Amazon &rarr;</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Choose X-T5 if…</h3>
          <p>You shoot mostly photos, love classic dials, and want 40MP detail with Fuji color. Video is secondary and
            you’re okay with a tilt screen.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn-buy" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
            style="margin-top:10px; display:inline-block; font-size:14px;">Check Price on Amazon &rarr;</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key differences</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Body & handling</h3>
          <p>X-T5 has classic dials and 3-way tilt; X-S20 has PASM dial and flip screen for video.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Video</h3>
          <p>X-S20: vlog mode, longer record limits, better thermals. X-T5: 6.2K open-gate but more rolling shutter heat
            sensitivity.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Stabilization</h3>
          <p>Both have IBIS; X-S20 tuning is more forgiving for handheld video, X-T5 for stills.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Choose X-S20 if…</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p>You shoot lots of video, need a flip screen, and want a lighter body for travel vlogs.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Choose X-T5 if…</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p>You are photo-first, prefer classic controls, and want higher resolution stills.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Bottom line</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p>X-S20 is the video-friendly travel body; X-T5 is the higher-res, photo-centric option. Pick based on whether
          you need a flip screen and long video takes, or the feel of dials and 40MP files.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Affiliate note</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p>This page may contain affiliate links. If you buy through them, we may earn a small commission at no extra
          cost to you.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  
    <!-- Author Box -->
    <section class="section author-box" style="background: var(--bg-soft); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; margin-top: 32px;">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start;">
        <img src="/assets/images/team-avatar.webp" alt="cameraupick Editorial Team" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: contain; background: white; border: 2px solid var(--accent); padding: 4px;">
        <div>
          <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">Written by cameraupick Editorial Team</h4>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">
            Our team of professional photographers and videographers has 10+ years of experience testing cameras. 
            We buy our own gear and provide honest, unbiased reviews.
          </p>
          <a href="../about.html" style="font-size: 14px; margin-top: 8px; display: inline-block;">Learn more about our testing process →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
